      • getCreationDate

        public Timestamp getCreationDate()
        The creation date is the date as this NoteStoringTO got constructed. If the note is an update it will be used as last modification date, and if it is a create as creation date.
        Returns:
        the creation date of this note, will never be null (is set on constructing or using setCreationDate(Timestamp)

      • setTransientProperty

        public void setTransientProperty(String key,
                                 Object value)
        Add a property which will not be persisted with the note. This can for example be used to exchange information between a NoteStoringPreProcessor and a NoteStoringPostProcessor.
        Parameters:
        key - the key of the property. If there is already a property with that key it will be replaced.
        value - the value of the property
        Since:
        3.5
